        <main>
          <h1 class="title">International Scholarships</h1>
          <nav class="primary-nav">
            <span class="nav-title">Admissions Home Page<i class="nav-toggle"></i></span>
            <div class="nav-links">
              <a href="/admissions/undergraduate/" class="nav-link">Undergraduate Degrees</a>
              <a href="/admissions/postgraduate-taught/" class="nav-link">Masters Degrees</a>
              <a href="/admissions/postgraduate-research/" class="nav-link">PhD Computer Science</a>
              <a href="/admissions/scholarships" class="nav-link">Scholarships</a>
              <a href="/admissions/quality" class="nav-link">Teaching and Research Quality</a>
              <a href="/admissions/international/" class="nav-link">For International Students</a>
              <a href="/admissions/undergraduate/open-days" class="nav-link">Open Days and Outreach</a>
              <a href="/admissions/contact" class="nav-link">Contact Us</a>
            </div>
          </nav>
          <p>The following awards are available to all privately funded international students applying for 2017 entry undergraduate programmes:</p>

<table class="table">
<thead>
<tr>
  <th>Scholarship</th>
  <th>Amount awarded</th>
  <th>Who is eligible?</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
  <td>Achievement Scholarship</td>
  <td>£1,500</td>
  <td>International students who attain AAA or equivalent qualification on entry.  <strong>Renewable annually, subject to obtaining full credits and an overall yearly mark of 70% or higher on the first attempt</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Excellence Scholarship</td>
  <td>An additional £1,500</td>
  <td>International students who attain A*AA/AAAA or equivalent qualification on entry. <strong>Not renewable.  The Excellence Scholarship is awarded for first year only</strong></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p><bk></p>

<p>There is no special application process – the awards will be made automatically to all eligible students admitted to the School of 
Computer Science who apply by the end of July to commence their studies in the September of year of entry.</p>

<p>Students who are in receipt of support from other funding bodies which wholly cover their tuition fees are not eligible for 
any of the awards. Students in receipt of part-funding should contact the <a href="&#109;&#x61;&#105;&#x6c;&#116;&#x6f;&#58;&#x75;&#103;&#x2d;&#97;&#x64;&#109;&#x69;&#115;&#x73;&#105;&#x6f;&#110;&#x73;&#64;&#x63;s&#46;&#x62;&#104;&#x61;&#109;&#x2e;&#97;&#x63;&#46;&#x75;&#107;">Admissions Tutor</a> to check their eligibility.</p>

<h2>University of Birmingham Scholarships</h2>

<p>The University has a range of funding opportunities available to eligible international students. Please <a href="http://www.birmingham.ac.uk/undergraduate/funding/index.aspx">click here</a> for further information.</p>

<h2>Please Note:</h2>

<ul>
<li><strong>Scholarships are subject to change</strong></li>
<li><strong>Scholarships are awarded at the discretion of the School</strong></li>
<li><strong>Further conditions will apply. These will be specified in the scholarship offer letter</strong></li>
</ul>

<hr />

